parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Belt and seal failures can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents and safety risks.
symptoms: Timing belt failure; drive belt failure; camshaft seal failure; crank seal failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Catalytic converter issues can cause overheating, fires, and safety risks to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Catalytic converter burning red hot; smoke coming from the back of the car; brakes failing; car catching fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Muffler failure can cause noise and potentially lead to safety risks due to decreased visibility and increased risk of accidents.
The breakage of the clutch fork can cause the transmission to jam, making the clutch inoperable, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the CV boots can cause premature wear on the CV joints, leading to vibrations, noise, and potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the clutch to become inoperable, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the transmission torque converter can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, stalling, or accidents.
The failure of the slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission axle seals can cause fluid leaks, leading to premature wear on the transmission and potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, stalling, or accidents.
